    "description": "Vijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners has an exciting opening for a Consultant Physician at our Srinagar office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Vijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners:\nVijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Post Graduate Diploma in relevant field\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Referral bonus program\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Srinagar, Jammu & Kashmir, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Vijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners!",
